4. Monetized Use attribution

If You engage in Monetized Use, You must provide clear, reasonably prominent, and readily accessible attribution to the Original Repository.

The attribution must:

(a) state that the product, service, or work is based on or derived from olnk.tr;

(b) identify the original source code using the full address:
https://github.com/MRsuffixx/OlnkTR; and

(c) make that address a working hyperlink when the medium supports hyperlinks.

The attribution must appear in at least one persistent location that users or customers can reasonably find, such as an About, Credits, Legal, Documentation, or application footer page. For command-line tools, libraries, server-only software, or distributions without a user interface, the attribution must appear in the primary documentation or other materials delivered to customers or users.

The wording may be translated or adapted to the surrounding language, but it must accurately communicate the relationship to olnk.tr and must not imply endorsement by the copyright holders.

Attribution in source code alone does not satisfy this section for Monetized Use unless the Software has no users, customers, interface, documentation, or distributed materials through which attribution can reasonably be provided.

